# Steps to Set Up a Maven Project with Selenium

## 1. Create a Maven Project
- Create a Java project.
- Use Maven to create the project from an archetype.
- Select the `maven-archetype-quickstart` archetype.
    - Use the following details:
        - Version: `1.4`
        - Group ID: `com.example`
        - Artifact ID: `first-maven-project`
        - Version: `1.0.0`
        - Confirm with `Y`.

## 2. Rename `App.java` to `Helloworld.java`
- Rename the `App.java` file to `Helloworld.java`.
- Copy the Helloworld code into the file (without the `set property`).

## 3. Open `pom.xml` and Add Selenium Dependency
- Modify the Maven compiler plugin configuration:
    - Change the Java version from `1.7` to `17`.
- Go to the [MVN Repository](https://mvnrepository.com/) and search for `Selenium Java 4.31.0`.
- Copy the XML dependency for Selenium and paste it into the `<dependencies>` section of `pom.xml`.

## 4. MVN Commands

- `mvn compile` | Compila il codice sorgente (`src/main/java`)
- `mvn test` | Esegue i test unitari (`src/test/java`)
- `mvn package` | Compila, testa e crea il file `.jar` o `.war` nella cartella `target/`
- `mvn clean` | Cancella la cartella `target/` e tutti i file generati
- `mvn install` | Installa il pacchetto nel repository locale (`~/.m2/repository`)
- `mvn dependency:resolve` | Scarica e aggiorna tutte le dipendenze dichiarate nel `pom.xml`